text: Manfred Weinreich (born 28 September 1946) is a German rower who represented West Germany. He competed at the 1968 Summer Olympics in Mexico City with the men's coxless four where they came sixth. At the 1969 European Rowing Championships in Klagenfurt, he won bronze with the men's eight. ==References== Category:1946 births Category:Living people Category:German male rowers Category:Olympic rowers of West Germany Category:Rowers at the 1968 Summer Olympics Category:People from Aurich (district) Category:European Rowing Championships medalists
